# Vault Brain OS — Context Loading

Vault path: `docs/knowledge/`. This is the Project Brain. Prefer it over scanning the repo.

## Mandatory load order

1. `docs/knowledge/00_HOME.md`
2. `docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Current-Context.md`
3. Only architecture / feature / DB / API notes relevant to the task
4. Only source files directly involved in the change

## Hard limits

- Never scan the entire repository unless the user explicitly requests it
- If context is missing, create or update the appropriate vault note instead of dumping more code into context
- Keep `15_MEMORY/Current-Context.md` updated when the working focus changes
- Every architectural decision, feature, bug fix, migration, and API change must be reflected in the vault before the task is complete

## Dual-layer content

- Human feature/architecture docs: clear Obsidian prose
- `15_MEMORY/*` and slim `AGENTS.md`: caveman-compressed
- Chat replies: follow caveman-always rule

## Do not

- Bypass Home/Current Context “to go faster”
- Re-introduce a fat AGENTS.md dump
- Store secrets in vault notes
